  "title": "Semantic Kernel SessionsPythonPlugin arbitrary file read/write via path traversal",
  "description": "The SessionsPythonTool plugin in Microsoft Semantic Kernel exposes upload_file and download_file kernel functions that accept a local_file_path parameter from the AI agent. Both functions pass this path directly to open() without any validation or path canonicalization. An attacker who controls the agent's tool-call arguments can use path traversal sequences (e.g., ../../etc/passwd) to read arbitrary files via upload_file or overwrite arbitrary files via download_file.",
